definition.value: IRIDA (Iron-refractory iron deficiency anemia) syndrome is a rare autosomal recessive iron metabolism disorder characterized by iron deficiency anemia (hypochromic, microcytic) that is often unresponsive to oral iron intake and partially responsive to parenteral iron treatment.

Leukonychia totalis - acanthosis-nigricans-like lesions - abnormal hair

definition.value: Hall-Riggs syndrome is a very rare syndrome consisting of microcephaly with facial dysmorphism, spondylometaepiphyseal dysplasia and severe intellectual deficit.

label.value: obsolete_autosomal dominant proximal spinal muscular atrophy

definition.value: Hartnup disease is a rare metabolic disorder belonging to the neutral aminoacidurias and characterized by abnormal renal and gastrointestinal transport of neutral amino acids (tryptophan, alanine, asparagine, glutamine, histidine, isoleucine, leucine, phenylalanine, serine, threonine, tyrosine and valine).

label.value: Cavernous hemangiomas of face - supraumbilical midline raphe

definition.value: Isolated hemihyperplasia is a rare overgrowth syndrome characterized by an asymmetric regional body overgrowth, involving at least one limb, and associated with an increased risk of developing embryonal tumors principally nephroblastoma (see this term) and hepoblastoma.

label.value: obsolete_46,XX ovotesticular disorder of sex development

definition.value: 46,XX ovotesticular disorder of sex development (46,XX ovotesticular DSD) is characterized by histologically confirmed testicular and ovarian tissue in an individual with a 46,XX karyotype.

label.value: Diaphragmatic defect - limb deficiency - skull defect

definition.value: Donnai-Barrow syndrome (DBS) is a rare, often severe, multiple congenital malformation syndrome with typical facial dysmorphism, ocular findings, hearing loss, agenesis of the corpus callosum, and variable intellectual disability. Congenital diaphragmatic hernia (CDH) and/or omphalocele are common (see these terms).
